18/08/2003
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano was reported in good condition on Sunday (17 August) after undergoing an operation to remove gallstones. 
He may be released as early as Monday to assume his duties. 
Nano spent the past week in Istanbul, where he attended the wedding of Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan's son on 10 August. 
(AFP, ATA, BBC - 17/08/03)
